cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.LG

The paper discusses topics related to program verification, including the design and algorithms of a verification condition generator, formalizing transformations into a functional language, describing the semantics of procedural languages, incremental verification, and detecting unreachable code. These topics are closely related to the sub-categories of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Software Engineering (cs.SE), Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL), and Learning (cs.LG).
